article.headline: Fordham 38, Georgetown 30
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Larry Dortch ran for three touchdowns and quarterback John Skelton passed for two more as Fordham beat Georgetown 38-30 on Saturday. Dortch carried 31 times for 127 yards and scored on runs of 4-, 1- and 2 yards for the Rams (3-8). Skelton completed 14-of-24 passes for 288 yards. Georgetown finished its season 2-9. Matt Bassuener threw for 245 yards and three touchdowns with one interception. Georgetown opened the scoring when Charlie Houghton caught an 18-yard TD pass. Houghton finished with 91 yards rushing and three catches for 24 yards. The Hoyas built a 21-10 advantage on Matt Burgner's 5-yard run with 52 seconds left in the first half. Fordham then scored three touchdowns to take a 31-21 lead after three quarters. Skelton threw a 5-yard scoring pass to Ty Hogan and Dortch added a pair of scores, including a 2-yard TD run with 5 seconds left in the third quarter.
